==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crick
<hw>Crick</hw> <pr>(kr⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Creak</er>.]</ety> <def>The creaking of a door, or a noise
resembling it.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crick</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Crick
<hw>Crick</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[The same as <ets>creek</ets> a
bending, twisting. See <er>Creek</er>, <er>Crook</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A painful, spasmodic affection of the muscles of some
part of the body, as of the neck or back, rendering it difficult to move
the part.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q> To those also that, with a <qex>crick</qex> or cramp, have thei
necks drawn backward.</q> <rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>cric</ets>.]</ety> <def>A small
jackscrew.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cricket</ent>⟦br⟧
